      "title": "Module 2 — The predictable external high-risk situations",
      "text": "A handful of situations carry elevated risk for almost everyone. Naming them and pre-planning removes most of their danger:\n\n• Celebrations and parties: alcohol, other smokers, festive \"rules don't count tonight\" thinking. Plan: decide before you arrive (sober) that no puff happens; keep a drink/food in hand; have your refusal line ready.\n\n• Crises and grief: the moment someone says \"here, this'll calm you,\" or your own mind offers the cigarette as comfort. Plan: remember it gives only a momentary, false boost while restarting the trap; reach for a real comfort (a person, air, movement) instead.\n\n• Travel and disruption: broken routine, boredom, stress, duty-free everywhere, \"I'm on holiday\" thinking. Plan: pack your tools and your reasons; freedom isn't on holiday.\n\n• Being around a specific heavy-smoking person or place. Plan: go in with the trap clearly in mind and your indifference rehearsed."
